17 (3) The governor shall appoint the members of the strategic
18 advisory board described under subsection (2)(b) within 90 days
19 after the effective date of the amendatory act that added this
20 section.
21 (4) The term of a member of the strategic advisory board is 1
22 year or until a successor is appointed under subsection (2),
23 whichever is later, but not to exceed the time period it takes the
24 strategic advisory board to develop the strategic plan in
25 accordance with section 9c.
26 (5) If a vacancy occurs on the strategic advisory board, the
27 governor shall appoint an individual to fill the vacancy for the
28 balance of the term.
29 (6) The governor may remove a member of the strategic advisory
KAS S01171'25 (S-5) suqeoh

9
1 board for incompetence, dereliction of duty, malfeasance,
2 misfeasance, or nonfeasance in office, or any other good cause.
3 (7) The individuals appointed under subsection (2)(b) shall
4 call the first meeting of the strategic advisory board. At the
5 first meeting, the nonvoting members appointed under subsection
6 (2)(b) shall elect the voting members under subsection (2)(a) as
7 follows:
8 (a) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(i)
9 shall elect 4 of its own members listed under subsection (2)(b)(i)
10 to serve as voting members under subsection (2)(a)(i).
11 (b) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(ii)
12 shall elect 4 of its own members listed under subsection (2)(b)(ii)
13 to serve as voting members under subsection (2)(a)(ii).
14 (c) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(iii)
15 shall elect 4 of its own members listed under subsection (2)(b)(iii)
16 to serve as voting members under subsection (2)(a)(iii).
17 (d) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(iv)
18 shall elect 4 of its own members listed under subsection (2)(b)(iv)
19 to serve as voting members under subsection (2)(a)(iv).
20 (e) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(v)
21 shall elect 4 of its own members listed under subsection (2)(b)(v)
22 to serve as voting members under subsection (2)(a)(v).
23 (f) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(vi)
24 shall elect 4 of its own members listed under subsection (2)(b)(vi)
25 to serve as voting members under subsection (2)(a)(vi).
26 (g) The nonvoting members described in subsection (2)(b)(vii)
