4 (8) After the voting members have been elected at the first
5 meeting, the voting members of the strategic advisory board shall
6 elect a member as a chairperson and may elect other officers that
7 it considers necessary or appropriate. The governor may appoint 1
8 of the voting members to serve as a co-chair of the strategic
9 advisory board. The strategic advisory board shall meet at least
10 quarterly, or more frequently at the call of the chairperson or co-
11 chair if appointed or at the request of 10 or more members.
12 (9) A majority of the voting members of the strategic advisory
13 board constitute a quorum for transacting business. A vote in favor
14 by a majority of the voting members of the strategic advisory board
15 serving is required for any action of the strategic advisory board.
16 (10) The strategic advisory board shall conduct its business
17 in compliance with the open meetings act, 1976 PA 267, MCL 15.261
18 to 15.275.
19 (11) A writing that is prepared, owned, used, possessed, or
20 retained by the strategic advisory board in performing an official
21 function is subject to the freedom of information act, 1976 PA 442,
22 MCL 15.231 to 15.246.
23 (12) A member of the strategic advisory board is not entitled
24 to compensation for service on the strategic advisory board, but
25 the strategic advisory board may reimburse a member for actual and
26 necessary expenses incurred in serving.
27 (13) Only the voting members of the strategic advisory board
28 shall develop a strategic plan in accordance with section 9c with
29 advice and collaboration from the nonvoting members as described in
KAS S01171'25 (S-5) suqeoh

11
1 this section.
2 (14) In addition, the strategic advisory board may do either
3 of the following:
4 (a) Take any other action necessary to achieve the purposes of
5 section 9c.
6 (b) Perform any other duties or exercise any other powers
7 assigned to the strategic advisory board by law.
8 (15) Once the strategic advisory board develops and submits
9 the strategic plan in accordance with section 9c, the strategic
10 advisory board is dissolved and shall cease operations.
11 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
12 unless Senate Bill No. 213 of the 103rd Legislature is enacted into
13 law.
